eturns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.Number.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Simple decorator to add a __number__ property to a function\n\nUsage: @number(\"1.1\")\n\nThis field will then be used to sort the test results on Gradescope."]}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.Visibility", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.Visibility.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "val", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.Visibility.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Simple decorator to add a __visibility__ property to a function\n\nUsage: @visibility(\"hidden\")\n\nOptions for the visibility field are as follows:\n\n- `hidden`: test case will never be shown to students\n- `after_due_date`: test case will be shown after the assignment's due date has passed.\n  If late submission is allowed, then test will be shown only after the late due date.\n- `after_published`: test case will be shown only when the assignment is explicitly published from the \"Review Grades\" page\n- `visible` (default): test case will always be shown"]}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.HideErrors", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.HideErrors.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "val", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.HideErrors.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Simple decorator to add a __hide_errors__ property to a function\n\nUsage: @hide_errors(\"Error message to be shown upon test failure\")\n\nUsed to hide the particular source of an error which caused a test to fail.\nOtherwise, a test's particular assertions can be seen by students."]}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.Tags", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.Tags.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.Tags.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Simple decorator to add a __tags__ property to a function\n\nUsage: @tags(\"concept1\", \"concept2\")"]}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.Leaderboard", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.Leaderboard.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "column_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sort_order", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.Leaderboard.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Decorator that indicates that a test corresponds to a leaderboard column\n\nUsage: @leaderboard(\"high_score\"). The string parameter indicates\nthe name of the column on the leaderboard\n\nThen, within the test, set the value by calling\nkwargs['set_leaderboard_value'] with a value. You can make this convenient by\nexplicitly declaring a set_leaderboard_value keyword argument, eg.\n\n```\ndef test_highscore(set_leaderboard_value=None):\n    set_leaderboard_value(42)\n```"]}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.ImageResult", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.ImageResult.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.ImageResult.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Decorator that allows the setting of image data to be rendered in the test results\n\nUsage: @ImageResult\n\nThen, within the test, make sure the final two parameters are `encode_image_data` and `set_image_data`.\n\n`encode_image_data` takes an *absolute* path to the image to load and returns the base-64 encoded version of that image.\n\n`set_image_data` takes the label for the image, the actual data for the image, and the image type (default is png) and sets it within the result for further processing\n"]}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.PartialCredit", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.PartialCredit.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "weight", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.PartialCredit.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Decorator that indicates that a test allows partial credit\n\nUsage: @partial_credit(test_weight)\n\nThen, within the test, set the value by calling\nkwargs['set_score'] with a value. You can make this convenient by\nexplicitly declaring a set_score keyword argument, eg.\n\n```\n@partial_credit(10)\ndef test_partial(set_score=None):\n    set_score(4.2)\n```"]}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.OutputMessage", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.OutputMessage.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograder_utils.Decorators.OutputMessage.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Decorator that allows you to set a message"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "autograder_utils.JSONTestRunner", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "autograder_utils.JSONTestRunner.JSONTestRunner", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "autograder_utils.JSONTestRunner.JSONTestRunner.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "stream", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "descriptions", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbosity", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "failfast", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "buffer", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "visibility", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "stdout_visibility", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "post_processor", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "failure_prefix", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "result_builder", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "result_finalizer", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Set buffer to True to include test output in JSON\n\n\npost_processor: if supplied, will be called with the final JSON\ndata before it is written, allowing the caller to overwrite the\ntest results (e.g. add a late penalty) by editing the results\ndict in the first argument.\n\nfailure_prefix: prepended to the output of each test's json"]}, {"name": "autograder_utils.JSONTestRunner.JSONTestRunner._makeResult", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograder_utils.JSONTestRunner.JSONTestRunner.run", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "test", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Run the given test case or test suite."]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "autograder_utils.JSONTestRunner.JSONTestRunner.resultclass", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A test runner class that displays results in JSON form.\n    "]}], "exports": []}]}